text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia jamesiana is a tree or shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to an area in the Mid West, Wheatbelt and Goldfields regions of Western Australia.The tree or shrub typically grows to a height of 1.5 to 6 metres (5 to 20 ft). It blooms from May to November producing yellow flowers.
